    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the criticism, but isn't the main goal of those laws just to stop people from committing crimes in the first place? if a stricter sentence actually keeps a person off the streets and prevents them from hurting someone else, doesn't that make it a successful policy regardless of the sociological side effects?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
