    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you're almost saying that the \"tough on crime\" approach is inherently flawed because it doesn't fix everything at once. if a law successfully reduces crime in a specific area, shouldn't we call that a win for public safety, or is the \"systemic\" stuff more important than the actual crime rates?",
